DAPCHI, Nigeria - The schoolgirls kidnapped by the Boko Haram jihadist group in Dapchi, northeastern Nigeria, have been reunited with their families on Sunday, an AFP journalist saw. The schoolgirls were kidnapped on 19 February and released this week. READ:Â Nigeria's Buhari meets released Dapchi schoolgirls The 105 girls arrived at around 2:30 pm local time aboard five buses escorted by the Nigerian army to Dapchi, in Yobe state. They were greeted by their parents after spending three days with the authorities in the national capital, Abuja. AFP